msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:212
msgid "<strong>⚠️ Important Disclaimer:</strong> The Positive Investment List is updated periodically by the Indonesian government. Sector-specific rules may also be subject to additional conditions, licences, and partnership requirements. Always confirm current ownership limits for your specific business sector through a legal consultation before committing to an investment structure."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:223
msgid "Ongoing Compliance Obligations for PT PMA"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:225
msgid "Once a PT PMA is established, foreign investors have ongoing legal and regulatory obligations that must be maintained to keep the company in good standing."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:233
msgid "Quarterly LKPM Reports"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:235
msgid "Investment activity reports (LKPM) must be submitted through the OSS system every quarter (January, April, July, October). Reports cover investment realization, employment, and production activity."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:237
msgid "Deadline: End of each quarter"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:244
msgid "Annual LKPM Report"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:246
msgid "An annual investment activity report is required in addition to quarterly reports. This provides a full-year summary of investment, workforce, and operational data to BKPM."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:248
msgid "Deadline: January of each year"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:255
msgid "Annual Corporate Tax Return"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:257
msgid "PT PMA companies must file an annual corporate income tax return (SPT Badan) with the Directorate General of Taxation (DJP). Monthly tax payments may also be required depending on revenue activity."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:259
msgid "Deadline: April 30 each year"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:266
msgid "Annual GMS (General Meeting of Shareholders)"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:268
msgid "Indonesian company law requires PT PMA companies to hold an Annual General Meeting of Shareholders (RUPS Tahunan) to approve financial statements, ratify director actions, and make key corporate decisions."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:270
msgid "Required annually within 6 months of fiscal year end"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:277
msgid "NIB & Licence Renewal"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:279
msgid "Certain sector-specific business licences obtained through OSS may have validity periods and renewal requirements. Failure to renew on time may result in licence lapse and operational disruption."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:281
msgid "Varies by licence type"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:288
msgid "Capital Realisation Reporting"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:290
msgid "The progress of capital injection (paid-up capital) must be reported to BKPM as part of the LKPM reporting. Failure to show progress on capital injection may result in queries from BKPM and suspension of investment registration."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:292
msgid "Via quarterly LKPM reports"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:306
msgid "Foreign Investor Rights Under Indonesian Law"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:308
msgid "Law No. 25 of 2007 on Investment provides specific legal protections and rights for foreign investors in Indonesia."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:315
msgid "Investment Protection"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:317
msgid "Foreign investors are entitled to legal protection against nationalisation and expropriation without fair compensation, consistent with international investment protection principles."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:323
msgid "Repatriation of Funds"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:325
msgid "Foreign investors have the right to repatriate capital, profits, dividends, and other proceeds from their investment in Indonesia, subject to applicable tax obligations being fulfilled."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:331
msgid "Equal Treatment"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:333
msgid "Foreign investors are entitled to equal treatment under Indonesian law as domestic investors, except where specific restrictions apply under the Positive Investment List or sectoral regulations."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:339
msgid "Dispute Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:341
msgid "Foreign investors may choose Indonesian courts, BANI arbitration, or international arbitration (e.g., SIAC, ICC) for resolving business disputes, subject to agreement in contracts."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:355
msgid "Legal Risks Every Foreign Investor Must Know"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:357
msgid "These are the most common legal pitfalls that cost foreign investors their businesses in Indonesia. Understanding them prevents costly mistakes."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:363 page-foreign-investment.php:374
msgid "High Risk"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:364
msgid "Nominee Shareholder Arrangements"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:366
msgid "Using an Indonesian national as a \"nominee\" shareholder to hold shares on behalf of a foreign investor is <strong>illegal under Indonesian law</strong>. The nominee can legally take control of the company, transfer shares, or dissolve the business. Foreign investors have no legal recourse in such cases."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:369 page-foreign-investment.php:380
msgid "Legal Risk Details &rarr;"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:375 page-legal-risk.php:311
msgid "Director Removal Without Protection"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:377
msgid "A foreign director can be removed from their position by a shareholder resolution if the Articles of Association or shareholder agreement do not include adequate protective provisions. This can effectively lock a foreign investor out of their own company."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:385 page-foreign-investment.php:396 page-foreign-investment.php:407
msgid "Medium Risk"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:386
msgid "Sector Restriction Violations"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:388
msgid "Operating in a sector that is restricted or closed to foreign investment, or exceeding the permitted foreign ownership percentage, can result in licence revocation, forced divestment, and penalties. Always verify sector eligibility before investment."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:391 page-legal-risk.php:249 page-pt-pma.php:566
msgid "Get Legal Advice &rarr;"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:397
msgid "LKPM Non-Compliance"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:399
msgid "Failure to file LKPM reports results in administrative warnings and may lead to investment registration suspension. PT PMA companies that fail LKPM compliance may face difficulties renewing business licences and Investor KITAS."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:402
msgid "Compliance Support &rarr;"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:408
msgid "Inadequate Shareholder Agreements"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:410
msgid "A PT PMA operating without a comprehensive shareholder agreement leaves the foreign investor's rights (dividend rights, voting rights, exit rights) unprotected. Disputes become far more difficult to resolve without this document."
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:413
msgid "Contract Drafting &rarr;"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:418
msgid "Compliance Risk"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:419
msgid "Capital Injection Failure"
msgstr ""

#: page-foreign-investment.php:421
msgid "Failure to properly inject and document the minimum paid-up capital creates compliance issues with BKPM and may trigger a review of the company's investment registration — potentially affecting all licences and permits linked to the PT PMA."
msgstr ""

